reviews.review: "The circle is now complete..." What a surprising and emotional ride for a life long Star Wars Fan. J.J. Abrams is a master storyteller, picking up the shattered pieces of "The last Jedi" and crafting it into a satisfying ending for the old and new generation of Lucas's imaginative Characters. I found myself caring for the new team as they found their stride and camaraderie. I want to see more. Hats off. Childhood is complete.
Great movie from start to finish!
The ending ruined the movie for me. I liked it until the end.

Really dissapointing what has become of this franchise. The next story is a mess. You can see that nothing was planned after episode 7.  The actors did an amazing job for the poor script. The effects are nice but it's too be expected from a Star Wars movie. 

It's suppose to respect old characters and come to an end to the original trilogy which already had a satisfying ending. This extension just ruins what was established in the originals and doesn't make any sense.
I felt like I watched 4 movies in one. Not much of a plot and the dialogue was confusing. At times the movie was entertaining but by far not the best in the series.
So like Iâ€™ve watched and read Star Wars my whole life. This movie was garbage and seemed like it was written like some teenage fan fiction.

I was one of those people who didn't like The Last Jedi, but this movie I really liked. Can't wait to see it again, because it was a lot to process. I was glad to see Rey, Finn and Poe back together on a great adventure. Babu Frik is hilarious, the real star of the movie.

Highly entertaining and for its target audience it hits it out of the park. My 10 year old thinks it's the best movie ever. I think it's a great Star Wars movie. Just pure entertainment and fun. Wrapping up a 9 movie series, comics, novels, tv shows, etc... should be full of fan service. Anyone who says otherwise just doesn't understand the importance of pure entertainment especially for a series made for kids (of all ages).
Never again start a giant trilogy with no plan.

This movie definitely has high expectations from the audience and while it wasn't filled with many "unexpected" moments, it's a great end of an excellent saga. JJ puts together an action packed movie that keeps you going all movie long. Can't wait to See what parts of the story they fill in next.
